pi.name: Golnaz Habibi
pi.bio: Golnaz Habibi is a professor in the School of Computer Science at the University of Oklahoma. She is currently the director and principal investigator of AirLab. Previously, she was a research scientist at the Massachusetts Institute of Technology, a robotics engineer at Autel Robotics, and a control engineer at Nargon. Golnaz holds MS and BS degrees in electrical and control engineering from the Toosi University of Technology and Tarbiat Modares University, and she received her Ph.D. in computer science from Rice University. Golnaz is interested in machine learning, robotics, self-driving vehicles, reinforcement learning, multi-agent systems, and computer vision.

grad.name: Maisha Maliha
grad.bio:
Maisha is a Ph.D student in Computer Science at the University of Oklahoma. Currently, she is working as a Graduate Research Assistant under Prof. Dr. Habibi‘s supervision. She has completed a Master of Technology in Computer Science and Engineering from the Indian Institute of Technology Bombay, India by achieving a full-funded fellowship under the Indian Council for Cultural Relations Scholarship and a Bachelor of Science in Information & Communications Engineering from East West University, Bangladesh. She also worked as a Lecturer at a Polytechnic Institute under the Department of Computer Science and was a Graduate Teaching Assistant at East West University Bangladesh.

Her research interests are related to machine learning, artificial intelligence, IoT, natural language processing, computer vision and robotics. She loves to see the sunset and enjoys traveling to new places.

grad.name: Avinash Reddy Nuthalapati
grad.bio:
Avinash is currently a master‘s student in Computer science. He has an BTech degree in computer science from MRCET, India.

His research interest includes Application development and Generative Adversarial Networks.

undergrad.name: Daniel Vargas
undergrad.bio:
Daniel is a junior majoring in Mechanical Engineering and minoring in Electrical and Computer Engineering. He leads the development and optimization of robotics and drones and the implementation of autonomous navigation in the AirLab. He is a member of OU Powerlifting and is the secretary for Sooners Without Borders.

His research interests include mechanical optimization, autonomous navigation, robotics, and drones.

undergrad.name: Tyler Roman
undergrad.bio:
Tyler is a junior Computer Science student with a minor in Mathematics pursuing honors. Previously, he's worked in 3Sigma Lab at the University of Oklahoma, focusing on Computational Neuroscience. He is also the Leader of the Sooner Rover Autonomous Team, proud Henderson Scholar, and the cofounder of turnstyl.
His research interests lie in robotics and network communication

undergrad.name: Phong Nguyen
undergrad.bio: Phong Nguyen is an undergraduate student in the AirLab.

undergrad.name: Matthew Carroll
undergrad.bio: Matthew Carroll is an undergraduate student in the AirLab.

undergrad.name: Ethan Haque
undergrad.bio:
Ethan is a Junior majoring in Computer Science on the Accelerated Masters track while minoring in Mathematics, Economics, and Psychology. He is a freelance designer, which includes but is not limited to photography, graphic design, illustration, mobile app development, and UI/UX Design.
His research interests include: Autonomous Vehicles, Medical Imaging Technology, Computer vision, and Artificial Intelligence. During his free time, he enjoys grabbing refreshers in cafes with people, birdwatching, playing the piano, and digital painting.

alumni.name: Mahmoud Sami
alumni.bio: Mahmoud is a postdoctoral research associate working in the AirLab.

alumni.name: Manthan C. Chilweri
alumni.bio: Manthan is an undergraduate student in the AirLab.

alumni.name: Parisa Masnadi Khiabani
alumni.bio:
Parisa is a Ph.D. student in Data Science and Analytics at the University of Oklahoma. She has a BS in electronics engineering from the Shariati Technical and Vocational College and an MS in mechatronics engineering from the K.N Toosi University in Tehran. Previously, she was a senior automotive embedded software developer at Capgemini Engineering and an active safety system engineer at Saipa Automotive Research and Innovation Center.
Her research interests are robotics, autonomous driving, multi-object tracking, autonomous control, and real-time embedded systems.

Google Scholar Page

alumni.name: Yuki Zheng
alumni.bio: Yuki is a rising junior majoring in Computer Science and minoring in Math. She is also a multimedia assistant career major completer, with three certifications in adobe premiere, photoshop, and multimedia. She is currently the Sooner Rover publicity coordinator and member of the autonomous sub-team, a Society of Asian Scientists and Engineers intern, the Society of Women Engineers publicity chair, a Diversity & Inclusion Scholar, and the co-founder and co-president of the first Girls Who Code college loop in the state. She is also a Halliburton Women's Welcome and ME^2 mentor.

alumni.name: William Wilson
alumni.bio:
William is currently a master‘s student in computer science. He holds a Bsc in mechanical engineering and a minor in electrical engineering from the University of Oklahoma. He has developed software for the federal government and currently works as an embedded software engineer at the Advanced Radar Research Center (ARRC). He is currently engineering the next generation of radar systems.

His research interests include 3D visualization, image processing, sensor fusion, machine learning, and navigation. During his free time, he enjoys playing ultimate frisbee, chess, video games, working on his homelab, or rock climbing.

Website: mechaengineer.com

alumni.name: Tate Smith
alumni.bio:
Tate is a master's student in Computer Science at the University of Oklahoma. He holds a BS in Computer Science with a minor in Economics, also from the University of Oklahoma. He currently works as a software developer for Paycom. He is also the cofounder of the OU C3 Cybersecurity Club. This semester he is working on developing an AI agent for the board game Risk.
His research interests include machine learning, genetic algorithms, and reinforcement learning.

alumni.name: Raj Saha
alumni.bio:
Raj Saha is a student at The University of Oklahoma pursuing an MS in Data Science & Analytics. He graduated from Bengal Institute of Technology, India in 2016 and started his professional journey in TCS, India as a data analyst for over five years. He is passionate and proficient at data mining, data analysis and visualization, big data processing, predictive model building, and strategic decision-making to achieve business objectives.

During his tenure through TCS, he developed AI Chatbot, Product Recommendation Engine, Automated Loan Approval system and Sales Forecasting model. His research areas include data science, machine learning, deep learning and artificial intelligence.
